The paper discusses learning structured models for computer vision applications, specifically for image labeling problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of maximum margin techniques and structural SVMs, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The use of conditional random fields and approximate inference techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the theoretical hardness of exact inference in loopy graphs, which suggests that it may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
